theorem closure_interior_inter_interior_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (interior ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X)) ⊆
      closure (interior (A : Set X)) ∩ closure (interior B) := by
  intro x hx
  -- `interior (A ∩ interior B)` is contained in both `interior A` and `interior B`
  have hA_sub :
      interior ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ interior (A : Set X) := by
    apply interior_mono
    exact Set.inter_subset_left
  have hB_sub :
      interior ((A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) : Set X) ⊆ interior (B : Set X) := by
    apply interior_mono
    exact Set.inter_subset_right
  -- Use monotonicity of `closure` to obtain the desired memberships
  have hxA : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    (closure_mono hA_sub) hx
  have hxB : (x : X) ∈ closure (interior (B : Set X)) :=
    (closure_mono hB_sub) hx
  exact And.intro hxA hxB

theorem interior_subset_closure_self {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  exact subset_closure (interior_subset hx)
